                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Choate</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 9, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Choate states that Lord Lansdowne asks whether Manchuria is within the
                    phrase “neutrality of China” and whether it is under <pb facs="0416" n="328"
                        xml:id="pg_328"/> stood that Japan should preclude herself from activity in
                    that province of China in spite of Russia’s occupation and of which the latter
                    might make use as a base of military operations.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
